data.content:
It works. Here's the full program:

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Alice", 30);

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase,
    WriteIndented = true
};

string json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options);
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string name, int age);
```

**Output:**
```json
{
  "Name": "Alice",
  "Age": 30
}
```

`JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase` is a built-in policy (alongside `CamelCase`, `SnakeCaseLower`, `KebabCaseLower`, etc.) — no custom class needed. It converts your lowercase `name`/`age` properties to `Name`/`Age` in the JSON output.
